  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this randomized controlled study with stroke patients is to demonstrate that a
      re-education with interactive table with instrumented objects delivering sensory feedback and
      serious game improve certain motor functions of the paretic upper limb than rehabilitation
      based on a standardized self-rehabilitation program.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
